            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "OEM brands should set a minimum 85% conversion efficiency (3.7V→5V) as the acceptance criterion for mass production. The formula is: Usable mAh = (Rated mAh × 3.7V × Efficiency) ÷ 5V. At 85% efficiency, a 10,000mAh cell delivers ~6,290mAh usable. At 65% (budget circuits), the same cell delivers only ~4,800mAh, a 24% real-world difference from the same rated capacity. Demand the conversion efficiency test data per production lot. This specification directly impacts your retail packaging claims, customer reviews, and return rates. GaN-based power banks consistently achieve 90-92%, the 8-percentage-point gap vs budget circuits is the single largest quality differentiator in the power bank market."
